# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
#
# This is the single source of truth for all AI-assisted development.
# Every component, every line of copy, every design decision must
# conform to these rules. No exceptions without explicit instruction.


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 1. COMPANY IDENTITY
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Company:        Raven Tech Group
Type:           B2B technology consultancy
Founded:        2024
Headquarters:   Westlands, Nairobi, Kenya
Markets:        East Africa and West Africa (primary), Pan-Africa (growth)
Clients:        SACCOs, fintechs, growth-stage businesses
Founder:        Victor — sole founder, Managing Director
Website:        https://raventechgroup.com

POSITIONING:
Raven Tech Group is the technology partner for African businesses that
are serious about growth. Not a body shop. Not a generic IT company.
A strategic consultancy that builds, transforms, and secures the
technology infrastructure that ambitious African businesses run on.

TONE OF VOICE:
- Direct. Confident. Expert. Zero fluff.
- Write like a senior consultant speaking to a CEO — not a salesperson
  pitching to a procurement officer.
- Africa-forward without being tokenistic. Kenya and the continent are
  context, not a gimmick.
- Numbers over adjectives. Specificity over vagueness.
- Active voice always. "We build" not "Solutions are built."
- Never use: "passionate", "cutting-edge", "leverage", "synergy",
  "holistic", "seamlessly", "innovative", "best-in-class", "robust",
  "scalable solutions", "we help businesses grow"


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 2. COLOR STRATEGY — DARK-PRIMARY WITH LIGHT CONTRAST SECTIONS
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

DESIGN PHILOSOPHY:
The Kenyan B2B market defaults to light sites built on cheap templates.
Raven goes the opposite direction — dark, authoritative, premium — because
our clients are making serious technology investments and they need to
feel that Raven is operating at a different level. This is the same
logic used by McKinsey Digital, Vercel, Linear, and Stripe.

Light sections exist for contrast, breathing room, and long-form
readability — not as the default.

PALETTE:

  Primary Black:    #0A0A0A   — dominant background, 70% of the site
  Off-Black:        #111111   — elevated surfaces, card backgrounds
  Dark Surface:     #161616   — secondary cards, hover states on dark
  Border Dark:      #ffffff14 — subtle borders on dark backgrounds (8% white)
  Border Accent:    #ffffff1f — visible borders on dark (12% white)

  Primary White:    #FFFFFF   — text on dark, light section backgrounds
  Off-White:        #F8F8F7   — light section background (warmer than pure white)
  Muted Text:       #ffffff99 — secondary text on dark (60% white)
  Subtle Text:      #ffffff66 — tertiary text on dark (40% white)

  Amber Primary:    #FFA91F   — THE accent. CTAs, highlights, hover, active states
  Amber Hover:      #FFB83F   — amber hover (lighter)
  Amber Muted:      #FFA91F33 — amber at 20% opacity for subtle glows/backgrounds
  Amber Border:     #FFA91F66 — amber at 40% for card borders on hover

  Dark Text:        #0A0A0A   — text on light sections
  Dark Muted:       #0A0A0A99 — secondary text on light (60% opacity)

SECTION COLOR MAP — follow this exactly:

  DARK sections (#0A0A0A bg):
  - Hero
  - Services grid
  - Process / How we work
  - Stats / QuickFacts
  - CTA banners
  - Industries
  - Newsletter
  - Footer
  - Service individual pages (hero + main content)
  - Blog post hero
  - Careers
  - Audit / lead magnet page

  LIGHT sections (#F8F8F7 bg):
  - Testimonials
  - Case Studies index and individual cases
  - Blog post body content
  - Pricing page
  - About page (alternating)
  - Resources / downloads
  - Partners / Stack logos

  MIXED (dark hero, light body):
  - About page
  - Individual blog posts
  - Individual case studies

NEVER:
  - Use pure #000000 — always #0A0A0A
  - Use pure #FFFFFF for backgrounds — use #F8F8F7 for light sections
  - Use amber as a large background fill
  - Use more than one accent color — amber is the only accent
  - Use grey as a primary color — only as text opacity on dark


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 3. TYPOGRAPHY
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PRIMARY FONT: Manrope (Google Fonts)
- Load weights: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700, 800
- Never use system fonts as primary
- font-family fallback: 'Manrope', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif

TYPE SCALE:

  Display / Hero H1:
    text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-[88px] font-bold tracking-[-0.03em] leading-[1.0]

  Section H2:
    text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.1]

  Sub-heading H3:
    text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.01em] leading-[1.2]

  Card title H4:
    text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-snug

  Body large:
    text-lg font-normal leading-[1.75] text-white/80

  Body:
    text-base font-normal leading-[1.75]

  Section label (eyebrow):
    text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[#FFA91F]

  Caption / meta:
    text-sm font-medium text-white/50

  Stats / Big numbers:
    text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold tracking-[-0.04em] text-white

LETTER SPACING RULES:
- Tight tracking on large headings: tracking-[-0.02em] to tracking-[-0.04em]
- Wide tracking ONLY on uppercase labels: tracking-[0.12em] to tracking-[0.18em]
- Never apply wide tracking to body text or headings
- The contrast between tight headlines and wide uppercase labels is intentional


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 4. LAYOUT SYSTEM
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

CONTAINER:
  Max width:    max-w-7xl (1280px)
  Horizontal:   px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-12
  Center:       mx-auto
  Full pattern: <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-12">

SECTION SPACING:
  Standard:     py-24 lg:py-32
  Hero:         pt-40 pb-24 lg:pt-48 lg:pb-32
  Tight:        py-16 lg:py-20
  Between sections: no margin — sections flush, color change creates separation

GRID:
  Base system:  12 columns
  Gap:          gap-6 md:gap-8 lg:gap-12
  Common layouts:
    2-col:      grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2
    3-col:      grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3
    4-col:      grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4
    Asymmetric: grid grid-cols-12 — use col-span-7/col-span-5 for premium feel

SECTION ANATOMY — every section follows this exact structure:

  <section className="py-24 lg:py-32 bg-[#0A0A0A]">
    <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-12">

      {/* Eyebrow label — always present */}
      <div className="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <div className="w-6 h-px bg-[#FFA91F]" />
        <span className="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-[#FFA91F]">
          Section Label
        </span>
      </div>

      {/* Headline */}
      <h2 className="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white tracking-[-0.02em] leading-[1.1] mb-6 max-w-3xl">
        Section headline goes here
      </h2>

      {/* Optional subtext */}
      <p className="text-lg text-white/60 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed mb-16">
        Supporting copy. Max 2 sentences.
      </p>

      {/* Content */}

    </div>
  </section>

DIVIDERS:
  Between dark sections:    <div className="border-t border-white/[0.06]" />
  Between light sections:   <div className="border-t border-black/[0.06]" />
  Decorative accent line:   <div className="w-12 h-px bg-[#FFA91F]" />


SECTION SEAMS — soften every major boundary (no harsh horizontal cuts):

  Principle: When two full-bleed backgrounds meet — especially a scrolling surface
  sliding over a sticky hero, parallax, or imagery — a flat opaque edge reads as a
  visible seam. Blend with distance: gradient, translucency, and/or frosted glass.
  Tailwind arbitrary backgrounds only (no inline styles).

  Dark sheet / card over dark hero (#0A0A0A):
  - Prefer the wrapper to use a top linear-gradient: transparent at 0% → ramp
    rgba(10,10,10,α) → full #0A0A0A over roughly 12–18rem, then solid to the bottom
    of the wrapper (see app/HomePageContent.tsx scrolling column).
  - The first section inside may use bg-transparent so that gradient is not covered
    by a second opaque slab.
  - Optional: a short absolute bridge at the section top — backdrop-blur,
    backdrop-saturate, mask-image fade, subtle border-b and inset highlight — so the
    join reads as glass, not a ruler line (see components/sections/ServiceIntakeWizard.tsx).

  Dark ↔ light (#F8F8F7):
  - Do not switch bg in a single hard step across the viewport height. Use a short
    vertical gradient, overlap, or graded divider so the transition occupies vertical
    space; keep text contrast WCAG-safe.

  Light → dark:
  - Same: fade #F8F8F7 into #0A0A0A over a band — not an instant full-width color flip.

  NEVER:
  - A solid opaque block edge sitting on layered/sticky content with no soft join
  - Relying on identical hex colors alone to hide a seam — overlap and gradient still
    matter when z-index and motion separate the layers


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 5. COMPONENT DESIGN STANDARDS
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

CARDS (dark background):
  Default:  bg-[#111111] border border-white/[0.08] rounded-sm p-8
  Hover:    hover:border-[#FFA91F]/40 hover:bg-[#161616] transition-all duration-300
  Focus:    border-[#FFA91F]/60
  With bg number: text-7xl font-bold text-white/[0.04] absolute top-4 right-6

CARDS (light background):
  Default:  bg-white border border-black/[0.08] rounded-sm p-8 shadow-sm
  Hover:    hover:border-[#FFA91F]/40 hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-300

CARD CONTENT ORDER — never deviate:
  1. Icon or category label
  2. Heading (H4)
  3. Body copy (2-3 sentences max)
  4. CTA link or arrow (bottom)

BORDER RADIUS — Raven uses sharp edges:
  All components:  rounded-sm (2px)
  Pills/badges:    rounded-full (status badges, category labels only)
  NEVER use:       rounded-xl, rounded-2xl, rounded-3xl

BUTTONS:

  Primary (amber):
    bg-[#FFA91F] text-[#0A0A0A] px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold rounded-sm
    hover:bg-[#FFB83F] transition-colors duration-200 tracking-wide
    inline-flex items-center gap-2

  Secondary (ghost on dark):
    border border-white/20 text-white px-7 py-3.5 text-sm font-semibold rounded-sm
    hover:border-[#FFA91F] hover:text-[#FFA91F] transition-all duration-200
    inline-flex items-center gap-2

  Text link with arrow:
    text-sm font-semibold text-[#FFA91F] inline-flex items-center gap-2
    hover:gap-3 transition-all duration-200
    Use ArrowSwapRow.tsx for animated arrow

  Always use CTAButton.tsx. Never create one-off button styles.

FORM INPUTS:
  w-full bg-white/[0.05] border border-white/20 rounded-sm px-4 py-3.5
  text-white placeholder:text-white/30 text-sm
  focus:outline-none focus:border-[#FFA91F] focus:bg-white/[0.08]
  transition-all duration-200

  Labels:   text-sm font-medium text-white/70 mb-2 block
  Error:    border-red-500/60 + text-red-400 message below
  Success:  border-green-500/60

NAVIGATION:
  Position:   fixed top-0, full width, z-50
  Background: backdrop-blur-md bg-[#0A0A0A]/80 border-b border-white/[0.06]
  Links:      text-sm font-medium text-white/70 hover:text-white transition-colors
  Active:     text-white with amber underline border-b-2 border-[#FFA91F]
  CTA:        amber primary button, right side
  Mobile:     hamburger at lg breakpoint, full-screen overlay

FOOTER:
  Background: #0A0A0A, border-t border-white/[0.06]
  Layout:     Newsletter row → 4-col grid (Brand | Services | Company | Contact)
  Bottom:     copyright left | legal links right
  Socials:    LinkedIn, Twitter/X — hover amber

CLIENT LOGOS:
  Default:    grayscale opacity-50
  Hover:      grayscale-0 opacity-100 transition-all duration-300
  Never show colored logos in a strip


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 6. MOTION & ANIMATION
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PHILOSOPHY: Motion guides attention. It is not decoration.
Every animation must have a reason. Fewer, better animations.

CORE ENTRANCE — ScrollReveal.tsx, used on every section:
  initial:    { opacity: 0, y: 24 }
  animate:    { opacity: 1, y: 0 }
  duration:   0.6
  ease:       [0.21, 0.47, 0.32, 0.98]
  viewport:   { once: true, margin: "-80px" }

STAGGER (cards, list items):
  staggerChildren: 0.08
  delayChildren:   0.1

HERO HEADING:
  Use LetterFillReveal.tsx on H1 only
  Never on H2 or below. Never on body copy.

HOVER:
  Cards:    scale(1.01) + border color — not scale(1.05)
  Buttons:  color shift + arrow gap — no scale
  Nav:      color only — no translate

PAGE TRANSITIONS: template.tsx — do not touch

SCROLL-DRIVEN:
  - Parallax bg: SubtleParallaxBackground.tsx only
  - Counter animation: QuickFacts stats count up on viewport enter
  - Reading progress bar: on blog posts and case studies

PERFORMANCE:
  - Animate ONLY: opacity, transform — never width/height/padding
  - will-change: transform only during active animation
  - prefers-reduced-motion: wrap every animation with useReducedMotion()
  - No animation on off-screen elements

SKELETON LOADING:
  bg-white/[0.06] animate-pulse rounded-sm
  Use on dynamic content. Never spinners.


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 7. TECH STACK — LOCKED
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Framework:    Next.js 14 App Router
Language:     TypeScript strict — no `any` ever
Styling:      Tailwind CSS — no inline styles
Animation:    Framer Motion
UI:           Aceternity UI (spotlight, beam, card hover effects)
Database:     Neon PostgreSQL via @neondatabase/serverless
Deployment:   Vercel
Validation:   Zod on all API inputs
Packages:     npm

No new libraries without explicit instruction. Stack is locked.

IMPORT ORDER:
  1. React / Next.js
  2. Third-party (framer-motion, etc.)
  3. Internal components
  4. lib/data imports
  5. Types


