Never hardcode service data inside components.


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 12. INDUSTRIES — COPY SPECIFICS
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SACCOs & Cooperatives:
  Pain: legacy core banking, M-Pesa integration gaps, CBK compliance,
  manual loan processing, no member self-service portal
  Keywords: SACCO software Kenya, member management system, core banking
  Kenya, M-Pesa API integration, CBK compliance software

Fintechs & InsurTech:
  Pain: payment infrastructure scaling, KYC/AML compliance, cross-border
  settlement, unreliable APIs, micro-insurance product tech
  Keywords: fintech development Kenya, payment API Africa, KYC software,
  InsurTech Kenya, CBK sandbox, mobile money integration

Healthcare & Clinics:
  Pain: paper-based patient records, billing system gaps, lab integration,
  insurance claims processing, telemedicine infrastructure
  Keywords: hospital management software Kenya, clinic system Nairobi,
  healthcare IT Kenya, EMR system Africa, telemedicine development

NGOs & Development Organisations:
  Pain: donor reporting systems, programme data management, M&E platforms,
  disconnected field and HQ systems, data protection compliance
  Keywords: NGO technology Nairobi, development sector IT Kenya,
  M&E software Africa, donor management system, USAID tech partner

Logistics & Supply Chain:
  Pain: manual freight tracking, no real-time visibility, ERP gaps,
  driver and fleet management, cross-border customs documentation
  Keywords: logistics software Kenya, supply chain technology East Africa,
  fleet management system Nairobi, freight tech Africa

Real Estate & Property:
  Pain: manual lease management, no tenant portals, fragmented property
  data, payment reconciliation done in spreadsheets
  Keywords: property management software Kenya, real estate tech Nairobi,
  PropTech Kenya, tenant management system, lease software Africa

Growth-stage Businesses (catch-all):
  Pain: manual processes blocking scale, disconnected systems, no IT
  strategy, cybersecurity exposure as headcount grows
  Keywords: IT consulting Nairobi, digital transformation Kenya,
  business software Westlands, ERP integration Kenya, tech strategy Africa


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 13. COPY STANDARDS
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

H1:    One per page. Bold claim. Max 8 words. No full stop. Tight tracking.
H2:    Sentence case. Max 10 words. Statement, question, or fragment.
Label: ALL CAPS. Max 3 words. Amber. Wide tracking.
Body:  Max 3 sentences. Plain English. Benefit first, differentiator last.
CTA:   Action verb first. Specific. One primary CTA per section max.
Stats: Always include timeframe or source. Use + for approximations.

BANNED WORDS: passionate, cutting-edge, leverage, synergy, holistic,
seamlessly, innovative, best-in-class, robust, scalable solutions,
we help businesses grow, world-class (ironic given these rules)


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 14. LEAD GENERATION — CONVERSION ARCHITECTURE
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PRIMARY GOAL: Book a discovery call or request a free audit

CONVERSION POINTS:
  High intent:   /contact, /audit
  Mid intent:    /services/[slug] → "Start this project"
  Low intent:    Blog posts → newsletter + related service CTA

FREE TECH AUDIT (/audit):
  Covers: infrastructure review, security gaps, cost audit, digital readiness
  Form: Name, Company, Email, Phone, Biggest tech challenge (select)
  After: /audit/thank-you + email confirmation
  Stores to Neon via /api/audit

NEWSLETTER — "The Raven Brief":
  Single field: email only
  Stores via /api/newsletter
  Appears: footer, blog posts, homepage section 14

CONTACT FORM (/contact):
  Fields: Name, Company, Email, Phone, Service (select), Message (optional: attachment, marketing consent)
  After: /contact/thank-you

PRICING (/pricing):
  3 tiers, no prices shown — "Get a quote" links to /contact?tier=[tier]
  Contact form reads query param and pre-selects tier


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 15. BLOG SYSTEM
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

CATEGORIES: Tech for Africa | SACCO Tech | Cloud & Security | Founder Insights

BlogPost interface (lib/data/blogPosts.ts):
  slug, title, excerpt (max 160 chars), category, publishedAt, readTime,
  author: { name: 'Victor', role: 'Managing Director, Raven Tech Group' },
  content (HTML), relatedServiceSlug, seoTitle, seoDescription, ogImage

Blog index (/blog):
  Dark hero → category filter tabs → 3-col post grid → Newsletter
  Card: amber category label + title + excerpt + read time + date

Blog post (/blog/[slug]):
  Dark hero (title, category, date, read time, author)
  Light body (#F8F8F7) — optimised for reading
  Scroll progress bar
  After content: related service CTA → newsletter signup
  Schema: BlogPosting + BreadcrumbList + Person


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 16. API ROUTES
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

ALL routes must:
  1. Validate with Zod before any DB operation
  2. Return { success: boolean, message: string }
  3. Never expose stack traces in production
  4. Use try/catch on every DB call
  5. Return 400 (validation) or 500 (server) errors

DB tables (Neon):
  contact_submissions:    id, name, company, email, phone, service, message, created_at (budget legacy column optional)
  newsletter_subscribers: id, email, source, created_at
  audit_requests:         id, name, company, email, phone, challenge, created_at


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 17. ACCESSIBILITY
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Focus ring:       outline-2 outline-offset-2 outline-[#FFA91F]
  Images:           descriptive alt always — never empty
  Icon buttons:     aria-label required
  Forms:            every input has a <label>
  Motion:           useReducedMotion() wraps every animation
  HTML:             semantic elements — section, article, nav, main
  Skip link:        first element in body, visible on focus
  Contrast:         white on #0A0A0A = 18.1:1 (AAA) ✓
                    amber on #0A0A0A = 5.4:1 (AA) ✓


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 18. IMAGES & MEDIA
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Always:   Next.js <Image> — never <img>
  Hero:     priority prop — never lazy
  Format:   WebP for photos, SVG for logos, PNG fallback
  Max size: 200KB UI images | 500KB hero | logos as SVG
  OG:       1200×630px in /public/og/
  Video:    NEVER in repo — use Cloudinary or external CDN
  Logos:    SVG preferred — never raster for logos displayed >1x size


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 19. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=        # Google Analytics
  NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=     # https://raventechgroup.com
  DATABASE_URL=             # Neon — server only, never NEXT_PUBLIC_

  .env.local is gitignored. Never commit it. Set on Vercel dashboard.


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 20. ABSOLUTE RULES — NEVER VIOLATE
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  ✗ No `any` in TypeScript
  ✗ No inline styles — Tailwind only
  ✗ No <img> — Next.js <Image> always
  ✗ No Lorem ipsum — write real Raven copy
  ✗ No hardcoded copy in components — use lib/data/
  ✗ No animation variants outside lib/animations.ts
  ✗ No new UI libraries without instruction
  ✗ No rounded-xl or larger — rounded-sm only
  ✗ No page without metadata export
  ✗ No video files in the repo
  ✗ No DATABASE_URL on the client
  ✗ No components doing more than one thing
  ✗ No new route without adding to sitemap.ts
  ✗ No new page without StructuredData.tsx
  ✗ No pure #000000 — use #0A0A0A
  ✗ No pure white backgrounds — use #F8F8F7
  ✗ No amber as a large fill area
  ✗ No animation without prefers-reduced-motion check
  ✗ No harsh unblended seams between major sections — follow SECTION SEAMS in §4 LAYOUT
  ✗ No pushing to main without local testing


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# 21. GIT & DEPLOYMENT
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Branches:   feature/[name] | fix/[name] | content/[name]
  Commits:    imperative present tense — "Add blog index page"
  Main:       production branch — Vercel builds on push
  Strategy:   work locally, one clean commit per feature when ready


